						<summary>

						<p>Ruined Īśvara temple, north wall, right of entrance.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">••• ••• ••• Śaka 1219, Dunmukhi, Aṟpaśi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that Pūśandai dēvaṉ-āḻvāṉ alias •••• tērārtta-vēḷaṉ of Mākaral endowed 40 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> (as capital) for providing one <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of rice daily for (the food-offerings during) the <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> worship of Uḍaiyār Pāvanāśamudaiya-nāyaṉār. The money was left in the charge of <hi rend="italic">tānāpatigaḷ</hi> (executives) of the temple. </p>						

						</summary>
